HEADWORD: Gusty
<hw>Gust"y</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Subject to, or
characterized by, gusts or squalls; windy; stormy;
tempestuous.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Upon a raw and <qex>gusty</qex> day.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Gut</ent>⟦br⟧
